<!-- Chosen Palette: Custom - "Modern Tech Blue" (#F8F9FA, #DEE2E6, #495057, #0D6EFD, #0A58CA) -->
<!-- Application Structure Plan: The application is structured as a tabbed SPA with a sticky navigation bar for usability. This design was chosen to break down the dense information of the guide into four manageable, thematic sections: "Visão Geral" (high-level comparison), "Conceitos" (interactive diagrams for core mechanics), "Guia Prático" (step-by-step workflow simulation), and "Boas Práticas" (data visualizations). This non-linear, organized structure allows users to either follow a logical learning path or jump directly to the information they need, which is more effective for both beginners and those looking for a refresher than a simple linear document. -->
<!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 
- Report Info: Git vs. GitHub definitions. -> Goal: Compare -> Viz/Presentation: Side-by-side comparison cards. -> Interaction: None. -> Justification: Clearly delineates the two tools. -> Library/Method: HTML/Tailwind.
- Report Info: Git's 3-area workflow. -> Goal: Organize/Process -> Viz/Presentation: Interactive diagram with clickable areas. -> Interaction: Click on each area to display detailed explanations and associated commands. -> Justification: Makes an abstract process tangible and easier to remember. -> Library/Method: HTML/CSS/JS.
- Report Info: Branching and Pull Request flow. -> Goal: Organize/Process -> Viz/Presentation: Interactive step-by-step diagram. -> Interaction: Buttons to progress through the flow (create branch, commit, push, PR, merge), updating the visual state at each step. -> Justification: Demystifies the most critical collaborative workflow in Git. -> Library/Method: HTML/CSS/JS.
- Report Info: Best practice for commit size. -> Goal: Compare -> Viz/Presentation: Bar chart. -> Interaction: Hover for details. -> Justification: Visually quantifies the benefit of atomic commits over monolithic ones. -> Library/Method: Chart.js (Canvas).
- Report Info: Best practice for branch usage. -> Goal: Inform -> Viz/Presentation: Donut chart. -> Interaction: Hover for details. -> Justification: Provides a quick, impactful visual reinforcing that development should happen in branches. -> Library/Method: Chart.js (Canvas).
- Report Info: Code commands. -> Goal: Inform/Action -> Viz/Presentation: Code blocks. -> Interaction: Click-to-copy button. -> Justification: Improves usability by making commands easy to use. -> Library/Method: HTML/JS. -->
<!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
